      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "In a bowl, combine halved tomatoes, sliced onion (if using), minced garlic, olive oil, remaining salt, pepper, dried oregano and red pepper flakes; toss to coat.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Arrange the tomato mixture on the prepared tray to form a bed. Place the mackerel on top of the tomatoes and brush the fish skin lightly with a little olive oil and a drizzle of lemon juice.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Bake in the preheated oven until the fish is just cooked through and skin is crisp at the edges, and tomatoes are blistered and saucy—about 15 minutes depending on fish size. Check doneness by flaky flesh near the backbone.",
